<paragraph blockId="26.[163,1070,702,899]" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">
R e c o g n i t i o n The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DOLLFUSS" authorityYear="2013" box="[529,753,702,723]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="26" pageNumber="409" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="antropovi">
<emphasis box="[529,753,702,723]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">Ammophila antropovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by extremely large genitalia (3 × 
<quantity box="[362,424,731,753]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="409" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
), by the shape of the penis valve (
<figureCitation box="[770,859,731,753]" captionStart="Figs 461-470" captionStartId="165.[163,203,1486,1506]" captionTargetBox="[173,1055,225,1466]" captionTargetId="figure-1@165.[163,1070,204,1466]" captionTargetPageId="165" captionText="Figs 461-470: male genitalia: penis valve in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341211" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341211/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">Fig. 463</figureCitation>
), by the shape of the clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[256,347,760,782]" captionStart="Figs 198-205" captionStartId="146.[163,203,1501,1521]" captionTargetBox="[163,982,196,1479]" captionTargetId="figure-1@146.[163,982,196,1481]" captionTargetPageId="146" captionText="Figs 198-205: male clypeus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341173/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">Fig. 204</figureCitation>
), by the labrum with a preapical spine and the mandible with a basal tooth. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bytinski-Salz in de Beaumont &amp; Bytinski-Salz" authorityYear="1955" box="[409,583,790,811]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="26" pageNumber="409" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudonasuta">
<emphasis box="[409,583,790,811]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">A. pseudonasuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having a clypeal free margin narrowly emarginate (
<figureCitation box="[389,479,819,841]" captionStart="Figs 198-205" captionStartId="146.[163,203,1501,1521]" captionTargetBox="[163,982,196,1479]" captionTargetId="figure-1@146.[163,982,196,1481]" captionTargetPageId="146" captionText="Figs 198-205: male clypeus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341173/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">Fig. 204</figureCitation>
), the penis valve ending in a shorter spine (
<figureCitation box="[930,1020,819,841]" captionStart="Figs 461-470" captionStartId="165.[163,203,1486,1506]" captionTargetBox="[173,1055,225,1466]" captionTargetId="figure-1@165.[163,1070,204,1466]" captionTargetPageId="165" captionText="Figs 461-470: male genitalia: penis valve in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341211" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341211/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">Fig. 463</figureCitation>
), the gonostyle apically not broadened and not concave (
<figureCitation box="[719,810,848,870]" captionStart="Figs 390-397" captionStartId="160.[163,203,1504,1524]" captionTargetBox="[179,1070,225,1476]" captionTargetId="figure-1@160.[163,1070,204,1484]" captionTargetPageId="160" captionText="Figs 390-397: male genitalia: gonostyle in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341201/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">Fig. 397</figureCitation>
) and the labrum with a preapical spine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[163,1070,916,1491]" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">
D e s c r i p t i o n 3: 
<quantity box="[419,512,916,938]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" pageId="26" pageNumber="409" unit="mm" value="21.5">21.5 mm</quantity>
. Gastral apex without metallic shine. Black, following parts reddish-brown: mandible (except apex), clypeus next to free margin, ventral surface of scape, tegula, fore- and midlegs, hindfemur and hindtibia (except dorsal face), petiole venter, tergum I (dorsally black), gastral segments III-IV, segments V-VI (dorsally black). Clypeus, frons (nearly up to anterior ocellus), pronotal collar, pronotal lobe, scutum, all of mesopleuron, metapleuron (not so dense), propodeum (including propodeal enclosure) and coxa covered with appressed silvery setae. Head, thorax and propodeum (including propodeal enclosure) covered with whitish erect setae. Mandible inner margin with one preapical and one distinct basal tooth; labrum with preapical spine. Supra-antennal lamellate projection absent and episternal sulcus extending to anteroventral margin of pleuron. Clypeus elongate and narrowly emarginate (
<figureCitation box="[967,1058,1223,1245]" captionStart="Figs 198-205" captionStartId="146.[163,203,1501,1521]" captionTargetBox="[163,982,196,1479]" captionTargetId="figure-1@146.[163,982,196,1481]" captionTargetPageId="146" captionText="Figs 198-205: male clypeus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341173/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">Fig. 204</figureCitation>
), ventral half of clypeal disk slightly concave, dorsal half convex (
<figureCitation box="[882,978,1254,1276]" captionStart="Figs 332-356" captionStartId="157.[163,203,1391,1411]" captionTargetBox="[170,1049,224,1370]" captionTargetId="figure-1@157.[163,1070,204,1371]" captionTargetPageId="157" captionText="Figs 332-356: male clypeus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341195/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">Fig. 338</figureCitation>
). Vertex punctate, not covered with appressed silvery setae, pronotal collar dull, sparsely punctate, without transverse striae. Scutum punctate, some punctures confluent, scutellum longitudinally ridged and punctate; metanotum punctate. Propodeal enclosure coarsely punctato-rugose, slightly covered with appressed silvery setae and erect white setae. Pronotal collar laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[479,566,1407,1429]" captionStart="Figs 262-276" captionStartId="152.[163,203,1453,1473]" captionTargetBox="[172,1062,223,1433]" captionTargetId="figure-1@152.[163,1070,204,1433]" captionTargetPageId="152" captionText="Figs 262-276: pronotal collar of male in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341185" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341185/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">Fig. 270</figureCitation>
, dorsally: 
<figureCitation box="[672,760,1407,1429]" captionStart="Figs 307-319" captionStartId="155.[163,203,1514,1534]" captionTargetBox="[163,1070,205,1491]" captionTargetId="figure-1@155.[163,1070,204,1494]" captionTargetPageId="155" captionText="Figs 307-319: pronotal collar of male in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341191/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">Fig. 309</figureCitation>
. Gonostyle laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[978,1066,1407,1429]" captionStart="Figs 390-397" captionStartId="160.[163,203,1504,1524]" captionTargetBox="[179,1070,225,1476]" captionTargetId="figure-1@160.[163,1070,204,1484]" captionTargetPageId="160" captionText="Figs 390-397: male genitalia: gonostyle in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341201/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">Fig. 397</figureCitation>
; penis valve laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[399,491,1438,1460]" captionStart="Figs 461-470" captionStartId="165.[163,203,1486,1506]" captionTargetBox="[173,1055,225,1466]" captionTargetId="figure-1@165.[163,1070,204,1466]" captionTargetPageId="165" captionText="Figs 461-470: male genitalia: penis valve in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341211" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341211/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">Fig. 463</figureCitation>
, apically: 
<figureCitation box="[608,701,1438,1460]" captionStart="Figs 563-596" captionStartId="171.[163,203,1479,1499]" captionTargetBox="[174,1070,224,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-1@171.[163,1070,204,1459]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="Figs 563-596: male genitalia: penis valve in apical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341224" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341224/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="409">Fig. 579</figureCitation>
. Flagellomere I: II=1.6, length of petiole = hindtarsomeres I+II.
</paragraph>
